The Telegraph - Calcutta
 England-SA series dedicated to DOliviera
Durban: South Africa will honour one of the countrys greatest cricketers of colour, Basil DOliviera, by naming the forthcoming series against England in December-January after the player. The series against England will be played after South Africa return from India where they are scheduled to play a two-Test series in November. United Cricket Board of South Africa CEO Gerald Majola said in an interview on Monday that both the ODIs and the Test series against England would be dedicated to DOliviera. He said all future series with England would also be named after the player, who had to leave South Africa in the 1960s to gain international recognition in . (PTI)  Copyright 
